The paper deals with visual commonsense reasoning, which involves understanding visual scenes and answering questions based on common sense knowledge. This falls under the intersection of computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also proposes a new model architecture and discusses techniques for better text to image grounding, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on a benchmark dataset, which involves information retrieval (cs.IR) tasks.
